{{italic title}} [[File:LOC Court of Neptune Fountain by Roland Hinton Perry - 1.jpg|thumb| ''Court of Neptune Fountain'']] '''''The Court of Neptune Fountain''''' is a group of bronze sculptures, by [[Roland Hinton Perry]] in 1897-1898.<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!18226~!0#focus "The Court of Neptune Fountain, (sculpture)"]. ''SIRIS''</ref> [[Jerome Connor]] may have assisted in the manufacture of the sculptures.<ref>https://www.pbs.org/wned/elbert-hubbard/jerome-connor.php</ref>
They are located at the [[Library of Congress]], at [[Independence Avenue (Washington, D.C.)|Independence Avenue]] and 1st St S.E. [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref>http://dcmemorials.com/index_indiv0000192.htm</ref> The god [[Neptune (mythology)|Neptune]] is flanked by figures of the [[Triton (mythology)|Tritons]], each blowing a conch shell.<ref>[https://www.loc.gov/shop/index.php?action=cCatalog.showItem&cid=58&scid=514&iid=4052&PHPSESSID=c0eed9f05cd254bb8e8551c668a2827f "Neptune Fountain"], ''Library of Congress''</ref>
